<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="132" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">845.01/114½</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-06">August 6,
                                    1941</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I think you will wish to
                                give very careful consideration to this suggestion.<note n="12" xml:id="d132fn12">See memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of
                                    State, August 5, <ref target="#pg_179">p. 179</ref>.</note> In
                                my own judgment this Government is not warranted in suggesting
                                officially to the British Government what the status of India should
                                be, but were the President disposed to take the matter up I should
                                imagine that he would wish to discuss it in a very personal and
                                confidential way directly with Mr. Churchill.<note n="13" xml:id="d132fn13">Marginal notation: “I agree—CH”.</note></p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps">elles</hi>]</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>